 94: ## Tablas nuevas migration 015-025
 95: 
 96: ### `hr.invite_codes` (migration 015)
 97: 
 98: ```sql
 99: - id uuid PK
100: - code text UNIQUE NOT NULL CHECK(length=8)
101: - person_id uuid FK hr.people (cascade)
102: - generated_by uuid FK hr.people
103: - generated_at, expires_at, consumed_at timestamptz
104: - consumed_by_auth_id uuid FK auth.users
105: - invite_method text CHECK
106: - delivery_target, notes text
107: + 2 indexes (person_id, code WHERE unconsumed)
108: + RLS + 3 policies (select/insert/update solo hr_admin)
109: + 5 COMMENTs
110: ```
111: 
112: ### `hr.user_settings` (migration 022)
113: 
114: ```sql
115: - id uuid PK
116: - person_id uuid UNIQUE FK hr.people (cascade)
117: - notification_email_enabled, notification_in_app_enabled boolean DEFAULT true
118: - notification_whatsapp_enabled, notification_sms_enabled boolean DEFAULT false (v1.1)
119: - language text DEFAULT 'es' CHECK
120: - timezone text DEFAULT 'America/Panama'
121: - dashboard_layout, preferences jsonb
122: - two_factor_enabled boolean DEFAULT false
123: - created_at, updated_at timestamptz
124: + RLS + 3 policies (own or hr_admin)
125: + 370 rows backfilled
126: ```
127: 
128: ### `requests.tickets` columnas agregadas
129: 
130: Migration 019 (R8):
131: - `received_by uuid FK hr.people`
132: - `received_at timestamptz`
133: - `processed_by uuid FK hr.people`
134: - `processed_at timestamptz`
135: 
136: Migration 021 (R25):
137: - `manual_entry boolean NOT NULL DEFAULT false`
138: - `created_by_hr_admin uuid FK hr.people`
139: + index partial WHERE manual_entry=true
140: 
141: ### `files.uploads` (existente, constraint nuevo)
142: 
143: Migration 024: CHECK constraint en `category` con 13 valores válidos.
144: 
145: Estructura polimórfica:
146: - `entity_schema text` (ej: 'requests')
147: - `entity_table text` (ej: 'tickets')
148: - `entity_id uuid` (FK lógica al row específico)
149: - `category text` CHECK
150: - `path text` (storage)
151: - `mime_type, size_bytes` 
152: - `uploaded_by uuid FK hr.people`
153: 
154: ---
155: 
156: ## auth.users (R22 critical)
157: 
158: **Compartido entre apps**. NUNCA destructive ops sin filtro `allowed_apps`:
159: 
160: ```sql
161: -- ❌ PROHIBIDO
162: DELETE FROM auth.users;
163: 
164: -- ✅ CORRECTO
165: DELETE FROM auth.users
166: WHERE raw_app_meta_data->'allowed_apps' @> '["humanOS"]'::jsonb
167:   AND NOT (raw_app_meta_data->'allowed_apps' @> '["movimientOS"]'::jsonb);
168: ```
169: 
170: Encoding nota:
171: - **SQL directo** (Supabase SQL Editor, execute_sql, psql): `raw_app_meta_data`
172: - **RLS policies / Supabase JS / API**: `app_metadata`
173: 
174: Same data, distinto access pattern.
175: 
176: ---
177: 
178: ## Estado allowed_apps actual
179: 
180: - 48 auth.users totales
181: - 48 con `allowed_apps = ["movimientOS"]` (todos los actuales)
182: - 0 con `humanOS` (se incrementará al usar invite codes bootstrap)
183: 
184: ---
185: 
186: ## Convenciones RLS HumanOS
187: 
188: | Pattern | Cuándo usar |
189: |---|---|
190: | `USING (person_id = hr.current_person_id())` | Tabla con `person_id` dueño |
191: | `USING (hr.is_hr_admin())` | Tabla operacional de RRHH |
192: | `USING (person_id = hr.current_person_id() OR hr.is_hr_admin())` | Tabla con ownership + admin override |
193: | `USING (requests.can_view_ticket(ticket_id))` | Tabla relacionada a ticket (timeline, attachments) |
194: | `USING (hr.is_president_or_admin())` | Tabla configuración admin/president |
195: 
196: ---
197: 
198: ## Anti-patterns RLS
199: 
200: - ❌ Policy sin `TO authenticated` (default to all)
201: - ❌ Policy con `USING (true)` (sin filtro real)
202: - ❌ Policy sin WITH CHECK en INSERT/UPDATE
203: - ❌ Helper function sin `SECURITY DEFINER` + `SET search_path = ''`
204: - ❌ Helper function que llama `auth.uid()` directamente sin función intermediaria
205: 
206: ---
207: 
208: ## auth_id ↔ person_id vinculación
209: 
210: `hr.people.auth_id uuid FK auth.users(id)` — vinculación creada vía sign-up wizard.
211: 
212: Helper `hr.current_person_id()`:
213: ```sql
214: SELECT id FROM hr.people WHERE auth_id = auth.uid() LIMIT 1;
215: ```
216: 
217: Si `auth_id IS NULL` (persona en BD sin auth.user todavía): `hr.current_person_id()` retorna NULL → policies que dependen de `person_id` fallan → user no puede acceder a UI. Sign-up obligatorio.
</file>

