 133: ### Pattern A: Server action signature for `useActionState`
 134: 
 135: ```typescript
 136: // Pattern A — server action returns FormState para useActionState
 137: type FormState = {
 138:   ok: boolean;
 139:   message?: string;
 140:   errors?: Record<string, string[]>;
 141:   data?: unknown;
 142: };
 143: 
 144: 'use server';
 145: export async function someAction(
 146:   _prevState: FormState,
 147:   formData: FormData
 148: ): Promise<FormState> {
 149:   const parsed = SomeSchema.safeParse(Object.fromEntries(formData));
 150:   if (!parsed.success) {
 151:     return { ok: false, errors: parsed.error.flatten().fieldErrors };
 152:   }
 153:   // ... business logic
 154:   return { ok: true, message: 'Listo' };
 155: }
 156: ```
 157: 
 158: ### Pattern B: Server action import header for service role exceptions
 159: 
 160: ```typescript
 161: 'use server';
 162: // ADR-0006 exception: this server action uses service_role admin client
 163: // for multi-app provisioning. See docs/adr/0006-service-role-admin-client-onboarding-exception.md
 164: import { createSupabaseAdminClient } from '@/lib/supabase/admin';
 165: ```
 166: 
 167: Toda server action que importe `@/lib/supabase/admin` DEBE llevar este comentario header. ESLint rule `no-admin-client-in-client` valida que esta import jamás aparezca en archivos `'use client'`.
